Dated a little now, I had 2 versions of this game years ago. The first was on the PS2 and was great fun - a challenge but worth a pop. The second was later bought for the DS and to my surprise was much harder than the other version. Progress was curtailed and games over all too quickly because of the high difficulty. Sad to say that this is an excellent port of the latter. This 3 match style puzzle game is over all too quickly - okay for nostalgics, but there are better apps of it's type out there.

Unfortunately this isn't as cool as the DS version as it lacks a lot of 
stuff from it like missions and the boss scolding you in between finishing 
enough levels. It's still zookeeper, though so it'll always be fun to play 
and you can't really go wrong with buying this for a mere dollar.

Okay. I got this game after months of playing the free multiplayer. Been 
considering it due to the time constraints in the multiplayer making 
practice hard. I am confused as to why they don't upgrade this game to the 
graphics used in multiplayer. They aren't as crisp, nor does it flow as 
well. I'm unsure why the games can't be one one file. I like that this 
links me back into multiplayer, but wish multiplayer linked back here as 
well. Seriously though. Upgrade the graphics, my lord.
